					<description><![CDATA[<p>Funding targets next-generation identity security Oak has emerged from stealth with $60 million in seed funding to accelerate the development of its AI-native Identity Operating System. The company aims to</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/oak-raises-60m-ai-identity-operating-system/" data-wpel-link="internal">Oak Raises $60M to Build AI-Native Identity Security Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Funding targets next-generation identity security</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Oak has emerged from stealth with $60 million in seed funding to accelerate the development of its AI-native Identity Operating System. The company aims to unify identity governance and security by replacing fragmented legacy tools with a single platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Oak&#8217;s seed round was co-led by Accel, Greylock Partners and CRV, with participation from Hetz Ventures, AlphaDrive Ventures and several strategic angel investors. The startup plans to invest in expanding its engineering, artificial intelligence and cybersecurity teams.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by cybersecurity veterans Shai Morag and Tal Marom, Oak has already launched its platform commercially and says it is being deployed by </span><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/computer-science/enterprise-customer" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">enterprise customers</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The company believes identity has become the largest attack surface for organisations.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI platform replaces fragmented identity tools</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Oak&#8217;s platform is designed to provide organisations with a continuously updated control layer that governs every identity throughout its lifecycle. The system supports human users alongside machine identities and AI agents, reflecting the growing complexity of enterprise environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Instead of relying on static identity records, the platform analyses raw evidence from enterprise systems to build a live identity graph. It then evaluates actual access usage and automatically identifies unnecessary permissions and security risks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to the company, its AI-native architecture enables new application connectors to be created in hours rather than the months often required by traditional identity governance platforms.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tal Marom, Oak&#8217;s Chief Product Officer, said discussions with more than 100 chief information security officers and identity leaders highlighted widespread frustration with disconnected security tools and limited visibility into access management.</span></p>
<h2><b>Experienced founders target enterprise growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203568" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203568" class="size-full wp-image-203568" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-depicts-a-glowing-ho_KnpnziXCXW-VAj2_ldbhqw_gCmUsyZrRs6w4KbzzdDcXA_cover.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI-driven identity security and unified enterprise protection systems." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203568" class="wp-caption-text">Oak builds an AI-native identity platform to unify security, automate risk management, and scale across enterprise environments. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Morag brings more than two decades of cybersecurity experience to the business. Before launching Oak, he founded Integrity-Project, Secdo and Ermetic, all of which were acquired by major cybersecurity companies including NVIDIA&#8217;s Mellanox, Palo Alto Networks and Tenable.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Following Tenable&#8217;s acquisition of Ermetic, Morag served as the company&#8217;s Chief Product Officer before establishing Oak alongside Marom, who previously held product leadership roles at Tenable and Salesforce.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The startup has already assembled a team of around 50 employees and plans to continue hiring, particularly across the United States, where much of its future expansion will be based.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Oak says its long-term vision is to replace multiple disconnected identity governance tools with a unified operating system that provides continuous visibility, automated risk assessments and real-time remediation across enterprise environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/starlight-engine-raises-jpy-6-06-billion-fusion-energy/" data-wpel-link="internal">Starlight Engine Raises JPY 6.06 Billion to Advance Fusion Energy Demonstration</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Growing demand for AI-driven identity governance</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Identity management is becoming increasingly important as organisations deploy larger numbers of cloud services, connected devices and AI-powered applications. The company expects the new investment to accelerate product innovation globally.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industry analysts expect identity intelligence platforms to become a core component of enterprise cybersecurity strategies over the coming years as businesses seek better visibility into who and what can access critical systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Oak believes its AI-first approach positions it to address this growing demand by combining identity governance, risk analysis and automation within a single platform rather than relying on multiple standalone products.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/oak-raises-60m-ai-identity-operating-system/" data-wpel-link="internal">Oak Raises $60M to Build AI-Native Identity Security Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
